Package OOP_Project

  • Interface Summary 
    Interface Description
    Item
    The Item interface declares 5 methods that we implement in our product class.
    MultimediaControl
    This interface declares 4 methods and is implemented in MultimediaControl.
    ScreenSpec
    The interface ScreenSpec declares 3 methods that will be implemented in class Screen.
  • Class Summary 
    Class Description
    AudioPlayer
    The AudioPlayer class holds the 4 methods that are unique to all Audio Players.
    Employee  
    Main
    The main.java file holds information that works with the controller.java and the ProductLineDB.
    MoviePlayer
    The MoviePlayer class inherits Product and implements the methods from MultimediaControl who's body are filled in here.
    Product
    Product class is declared abstract and is used to declare all the generic attributes of a product(Id, type, name, manufacturer).
    ProductionRecord
    The production record class declares 5 variables, sets up geters and setters for them all in order to create a record for every product.
    ProductionTabController
    The controller class holds all the values from the objects being used in the GUI.
    Screen
    Class Screen implements ScreenSpec and fills in its method bodies.Then it creates a constructor called Screen which accepts 3 parameters and sets their values.
  • Enum Summary 
    Enum Description
    ItemType
    Enum ItemType declares the 4 types of products we will be storing to our database.
    MonitorType
    Enum MonitorType stores 2 values that we will use to describe our Monitor type.
